  "body": "Please provide as much information as you can: \n\n* **Suggested term label:**\np24 cargo receptor complex (Unfortunately this is the only name I can find)\n\n* **Definition (free text)**\n\nA cargo receptor complex localized to the Endoplasmic Reticulum (ER) exit sites, where it helps to select cargo for packaging into COPII vesicles.\n\n* **Reference, in format PMID:#######**\n\nPMID:32456004\nPMID:34647572\nPMID:27569046\n\n* **Gene product name and ID to be annotated to this term**\n\nSystematic ID   Gene name       pombe Product description     Budding yeast orthologs Human orthologs\nSPBC16E9.09c    erp5    COPII vesicle coat component Erp5/Erp6/Erp1     ERP1,ERP5,ERP6  TMED4,TMED9\nSPCC24B10.17    emp24   COPII-coated vesicle component Emp24    EMP24   TMED2\nSPAC17A5.08     erp2    COPII-coated vesicle component Erp2/3/4 ERP2,ERP3,ERP4  TMED3\nSPAC23H4.03c    erv25   COPII-coated vesicle component Erv25    ERV25   TMED10\n\n* **Parent term(s)**\n\nGO:0062137   cargo receptor complex\n\n* **Children terms (if applicable)** Should any existing terms that should be moved underneath this new proposed term?\n\n\n* **Synonyms (please specify, EXACT, BROAD, NARROW or RELATED)**\n\n* **Cross-references**\n* For enzymes, please provide RHEA and/or EC numbers. \n* Can also provide MetaCyc, KEGG, Wikipedia, and other links.\n\n* **Any other information**\n",
