      },
      "authorAssociation": "MEMBER",
      "body": "\nThe p24 cargo receptor complex is a conserved hetero-oligomeric complexes (often tetrameric), cycling ER–Golgi protein complex that selectively recruits secretory cargo, especially GPI-anchored proteins, into COPII vesicles and helps maintain early secretory pathway organization. A functional p24 complex typically contains one member of each subfamily of p24 proteins, alpha, beta, gamma and delta.\n\ndef synthesised form\nhttps://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19566487/\nand\nhttps://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26224213/",
