      "authorAssociation": "MEMBER",
      "body": "We do actually need this because it can't be decomposed. The entire complex has \"cargo receptor activity\"\n\n\nAnterograde (ER→Golgi): The p24 complex acts as a cargo receptor, packaging GPI-anchored proteins like Gas1p into COPII vesicles for forward transport.\n(this is the role I want to annotate in http://noctua.geneontology.org/workbench/noctua-visual-pathway-editor/?model_id=gomodel%3A693b3c0900004859\nI had to use \"cargo receptor complex\" but this is non specific, it has the child\"[GO:0062136](https://www.ebi.ac.uk/QuickGO/term/GO:0062136)    low-density lipoprotein receptor complex\"\n\np24 complex itself needs to be recycled back to the ER via COPI vesicles so it can pick up more cargo. The p24 proteins are assembled into heteromeric complexes that continuously cycle between ER and Golgi compartments. [PubMed Central](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC2265561/)\nThe p24 complex also has a role in  COPI retrograde vesicle formation [PubMed Central](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC2265561/),  p24 proteins are actively involved in generating the  vesicles that carry them back to the ER.",
